    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Description\n\nApologies if there has already been an issue for this - I couldn't find anything out there that seemed similar. \n\nThere are some occasions where I would like to be able to stop a specific LSP (like `eslint`), but leave all other language servers running on a buffer (`volar`, `tailwindcss`, etc.)\n\nCurrently, the only way that I know of to disable LSPs on a buffer is with `:LspStop`, but this stops all language servers.\n\nI think it would be a nice feature to modify this to accept LSP server names like `:LspStop eslint` so we can stop specific LSPs that are attached to buffer and leave all the others attached.",
